Moore Corp Ltd said it proposedamendments to a special resolution seeking shareholder approvalfor authority to issue preference shares, so that the shareswill be non-voting except in the event of dividend non-payment.    It said it proposed the amendments in response toshareholder concerns that under the existing resolution, votingrights could be attached to the preference shares that aredisproportionate to common share voting rights.    Moore Corp said it has no immediate plans to issuepreference shares under the proposed resolution.    The resolutions will be considered at the April 9 annualand special meeting, the company said. Reuter&#3;